    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Japan's Defense Minister resigned tonight after taking responsibility for a submarine accident last month in which 30 civilians died and which brought the military here under harsh criticism.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: Japan's Defense Minister resigned tonight after taking responsibility for a submarine accident last month in which 30 civilians died and which brought the military here under harsh criticism.</p>
        <p>Japan's Defense Minister resigned tonight after taking responsibility for a submarine accident last month in which 30 civilians died and which brought the military here under harsh criticism.</p>
        <p>The resignation of the official, Tsutomu Kawara, had been expected. However, Mr. Kawara awaited completion of an inquiry that largely blamed the vessel's captain for the collision with a fishing craft and concluded that Japan's submarines are ill-equipped to navigate in Tokyo Bay. Mr. Kawara was replaced by Kichiro Tazawa, former head of the Agriculture Ministry.</p>
      </block>
